We will be utilizing online registration this summer. We are currently in our final testing phase and hope to open up registration on Wednesday, July 15th. There are two things you can do to get prepared if you wish to get a jump start.

1. Make sure you have access to your Alma Parent Portal account (where you check grades for your students). If you do not have an Alma account, there are instructions in the link below to request access.

2. If you have a student that will be in Kindergarten, 2nd grade, 6th grade, 9th grade, and/or any student who will be allowed to take medication at school -- There are one or more forms that require a doctor/dentist/eye doc signature. Those forms are also available at the link below as well.

Please bear with us as there are bound to be hiccups and many questions with this new process. The registration page will be updated with more information and an all-call will go out to parents when registration is live. Feel free to reply with any questions and we'll make every effort to help. Thanks!

https://www.205warren.net/registration/

Hello, We will be hosting HS graduation Friday June 26th at 7 pm on the football field. Due to Covid-19 we are limiting the crowd on the field for the ceremony to just two people per graduate. We will also have the ceremony broadcast live on WCCI and we will be recording and potentially live streaming the ceremony for those viewers around the world.

post_text: Congratulations to Dr. Teske!
shared_text:
WIU Educational Leadership
April 9 at 3:07 PM ¬∑

Congratulations to Dr. Shawn Teske who successfully defended his dissertation entitled, Teacher Perspectives on Values, Motivation, and Leadership Through a Generational Lens" on April 9, 2020. Dr. Jim La Prad served as Shawn's chair and committee members included Dr. Stuart Yager, Dr. Pamela Rockwood, and Dr. Lora Wolff. Shawn (bottom center) has the honor of being the first defender during the COVID-19 pandemic . Shawn is the Superintendent and Elementary Principal at the Warren CUSD #205. Congratulations again, Dr. Teske!

post_text: Ms. Almquist, our music teacher, as well as, our 2nd Grade teachers, planned a week long unit to focus on the folktale, Peter and the Wolf. Students read and discussed the popular tale, as well as, listened to the very popular orchestra production of Peter and the Wolf. Students became familiar with the different instruments that created the characters in the classic Sergei Prokofiev‚Äôs symphonic tale. Our students enjoyed this music and literature collaboration!
